  "prompt": "Can one change branch from biotechnology engineering to engineering physics in IIT Roorkee?",
  "response": "Switching branches, such as from Biotechnology Engineering to Engineering Physics, at IIT Roorkee (or any IIT) is generally possible but is subject to specific rules, criteria, and availability. Here\u2019s how the process typically works:\n\n### 1. **Academic Performance**\n   - Your **CGPA** (Cumulative Grade Point Average) plays a significant role. Students with higher CGPA scores are more likely to be considered for branch changes.\n   - A minimum CGPA cutoff is usually set by the institute, and only students above this cutoff are eligible.\n\n### 2. **Availability of Seats**\n   - The number of available seats in the desired branch (Engineering Physics in this case) is a crucial factor.\n   - If there are more applicants than available seats, priority is given to students with higher CGPA.\n\n### 3. **Rules and Policies**\n   - Each IIT has its own policies and timelines for branch changes. These are typically announced at the end of the first year.\n   - The process may also involve certain restrictions, such as not allowing branch changes between certain specific branches.\n\n### 4. **Application Process**\n   - You\u2019ll need to formally apply for the branch change during the designated period (usually after the first year).\n   - The allocation is made based on CGPA and seat availability.\n\n### 5. **Other Considerations**\n   - Switching from Biotechnology to Engineering Physics involves a significant change in the curriculum. You\u2019ll need to be prepared for the academic challenges of the new branch.\n   - Ensure you have a genuine interest in Engineering Physics before making the switch.\n\n### Conclusion\nYes, it is possible to switch from Biotechnology Engineering to Engineering Physics at IIT Roorkee, provided you meet the CGPA cutoff, there are available seats, and you follow the institute\u2019s rules and procedures. It\u2019s advisable to consult your academic advisor or the institute\u2019s official guidelines for specific details and timelines.",
